^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|Although most people agree that with 4 hearts and 3 spades, opener should bid 2@H, some people play that opener should bid 2@S (responder is known to have 5 spades for sure).|
PG| ***** 78 ***** |


AT|

Basically, there are 3 schools of thought over how to respond to NMF when opener has both 3 cards in responder's major and 4 card in the other major.|
PG| ***** 79 ***** |


AT|

a) Always bid hearts regardless of whether responder's first bid was 1@H or 1@S (e.g. show 3-card heart support over 1@H and 4 hearts over 1@S). This is what you recommend in the movie and is the most common way to play,

b) Always show 3-card support.

c) Always show the 4-card major.|
